4. Beneficiary Handbook Section

A detailed guide written as if handed directly to students.

Welcome to the Scholarship

This handbook explains what you receive, what is expected from you, and how you can progress to higher levels of support.

1. Your Starting Point: JAMB Stage

You begin by receiving a free JAMB Form.
You must:
• Register correctly
• Sit for the exam
• Pass to move to the next stage

Support stops if you do not sit for the exam.

2. After JAMB: Securing Admission

If you pass JAMB, you will receive guidance on the following:
• Checking your admission status
• JAMB CAPS monitoring
• Choosing the right course
• Understanding registration requirements

You must present a valid admission letter before receiving any financial support.

3. Your First Funding: N100,000 Scholarship

When you gain admission:
• You receive N100,000 for your school fees
• Payment is made directly to your school or via approved channels
• If your fees are less than N100,000, the remaining amount is kept for later support
• If your fees are more, all N100,000 will be applied to your fees

4. How to Earn More Support
Full Funding (100 percent)

To qualify:
• Your first-year results must be first-class
• You must maintain a first-class CGPA each year
• Your conduct must be proper and your documents correct
• You must submit your results every academic session

Partial Funding (Up to 50 percent)

You qualify if:
• You maintain a CGPA of 4.0 or above
• You have no disciplinary issues
• You submit your results on time

5. Your Responsibilities

You must:
• Submit your results every semester
• Inform the scholarship team of changes
• Keep all your documents accurate
• Avoid misconduct
• Attend any scheduled mentoring or review meetings

6. Losing or Pausing Support

Support may pause or stop if:
• Your CGPA falls below 3.0 for two semesters
• You do not submit results
• Any document is falsified
• You violate integrity expectations

You may appeal if necessary.